A former Senator, who represented Ogun East Senatorial District in the 8th National Assembly, Buruji Kashamu, is dead. The former lawmaker, who was a factional governorship candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party in the 2019 election was said to have died after a protracted battle with the deadly COVID-19. He was said to have died at First Cardiologist Consultants in Ikoyi. Senator Ben Murray Bruce was one of the first few friends to break the sad news on Twitter. “I have just lost my good friend of forever to COVID-19,” he said. Details later… 